                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d348">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.114 St. Pierre-Miquelon/443: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bullitt</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-12-18T15:00:00+00:00"
                            >December 18, 1936—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received December 18—11:05 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1275. Department’s telegram No. 530 of December 16, 7 p.m. Foreign Office states
                    that it believes there will be no difficulty in having the word “foreign”
                    omitted from the proposed decree.</p>
                <p>The Foreign Office is obtaining from the appropriate government office the exact
                    definition of the term “alcool de traite”.</p>
                <p>The Embassy is advised by the Foreign Office that no reply has been received from
                    the Ministry of Colonies with regard to its proposals and that no definite
                    action will be taken until after consultation by the two Ministries. It says
                    that it is practically certain that nothing will be definitely done before about
                    the middle or end of January and in the meantime the decree of April 9, 1935,
                    remains in force.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bullitt</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
